Recorded in Nashville last September, this week’s episode of Walking the Floor captures a 50-minute conversation between podcast host Chris Shiflett and blues belter Delbert McClinton.
Both musicians were in town for AmericanaFest, with Shiflett playing a string of solo shows during the weeklong event and McClinton receiving the Americana Music Association’s Lifetime Achievement Award.
And boy, are we in a world of spectacle.”It was during of those international tours where he met a young John Lennon.
This was ’62; Pete Best was drumming… That night, John came in and we shot the breeze.
McClinton had met Clark in Texas, back when a young Clark would occasionally crash McClinton’s band rehearsals.